# 005 -- Sources panel

> **Ordering note.** This slice carries Part **U4** of the parent spec. It is
> sequenced after slice 002 (Part U5) because U4.2 hosts the polarization ellipse
> in the `AvaPlot` adapter and the Poincaré sphere in the WebView2 adapter, both
> delivered by U5.1 (`ChartHosts.fs`).

## Spec reference

- `C:\GitHub\Berreman\specs\0024\.spec-md` -- parent spec this slice belongs to (Part U4).
- Ancestor: spec 0022 (tested Avalonia-free MVU core; clone-swap deferred, §A.9 / AC-A8).
- Operator-plan source: `specs/0022/.manual/018-ui-wiring-plan.md` (superseded; codebase wins).

## Inherited from parent spec

### Binding constraints (from `.spec-md` ## 0)

These apply to every part of this arc, including this slice.

- **0.1 — Freeze the tested core.** The implementation MUST NOT edit any
  model / `update` / projection / persistence module under
  `OpticalConstructor.Domain`, `OpticalConstructor.Storage`,
  `OpticalConstructor.Optimization`, or the Avalonia-free logic modules in
  `OpticalConstructor.Ui` (e.g. `ConstructionPage.fs`, `StackEditor.fs`,
  `Workspace.fs`, `SynthesisFitPage.fs`, `JobRunner.fs`, `Schematic.fs`,
  `SystemView3D.fs`, `UserEnvironment.fs`, the `Charts/` and `Sources/`
  builders). These modules are Avalonia-free by mandate and carry the existing
  passing suite. New view code MUST live in **new sibling `*View.fs` modules**
  and the composition root. Adding a `Compile Include` line for a new file to
  `OpticalConstructor.Ui.fsproj` is permitted and is not an edit to a frozen
  module.

- **0.2 — Public FuncUI NuGet only; no clone reference.** All view code MUST be
  authored against the public MIT `Avalonia.FuncUI` 1.6.0 DSL surface already
  referenced by both projects. The implementation MUST NOT add a
  `PackageReference` or `ProjectReference` to
  `C:/GitHub/Avalonia.FuncUI.Clone/`, and MUST NOT depend on any clone-specific
  API. The clone-swap decision (spec 0022 §A.9 / AC-A8) stays deferred; this arc
  does not touch it.

- **0.3 — Public-Avalonia layout primitives only for docking.** Panel
  layout/visibility/dock MUST be rendered with public Avalonia
  `DockPanel` / `Grid` / `GridSplitter`. The richer drag-to-redock / floating
  chrome is the deferred clone's responsibility and MUST NOT be invented here.

- **0.4 — UI-thread marshaling for every off-thread dispatch.** Any `dispatch`
  invoked from a background callback (a `JobRunner` progress or completion
  callback, a file-IO continuation) MUST be marshaled onto the UI thread via
  `Avalonia.Threading.Dispatcher.UIThread.Post`. A direct cross-thread
  `dispatch` is a defect. Every effectful `Cmd` this spec introduces MUST honour
  this rule.

- **0.5 — Non-serializable handles live outside the model.** The root MVU model
  MUST remain pure and serializable. `CancellationTokenSource`, live renderer
  control instances (`AvaPlot`, `WebView2`), and the Avalonia
  `IStorageProvider` MUST be held in the view/host layer (a component
  `ctx.useState` or a host field), never as fields of the root model.

- **0.6 — Persistence facts (no new committable file types).** Committable
  project files are written as `<projectName>.ocproj.json` under the project's
  working folder by `ConstructionPage.saveProject`
  (`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/ConstructionPage.fs:229`,
  path built at `ConstructionPage.fs:225`). Derived `.binz` sidecars are written
  under a per-project `.sidecars/` subfolder via the single shared seam
  `Storage.Sidecar.derivedArtefactPath`
  (`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Storage/Sidecar.fs:36`,
  directory at `Sidecar.fs:30`). `*.binz` and `*.autosave` are already ignored
  in the repository root `.gitignore` (`.gitignore:336`, `.gitignore:340`) and
  `.sidecars/` carries no committable state, so this arc introduces **no new
  committable file type** and triggers no `.gitignore` override work. The
  per-user environment-settings file is user-local, not committed.

- **0.7 — Gate roster.** This arc adds two new gates,
  `.gates/OpticalConstructor/ui-smoke.gates` (new) and
  `.gates/OpticalConstructor/ui-tests.gates` (new), modelled on the existing
  command-gate format (`.gates/OpticalConstructor/constructor-unit-tests.gates`,
  `.gates/Berreman/build.gates`). Every slice in this arc MUST end
  `build`-green, `constructor-unit-tests`-green, `ui-smoke`-green, and (once the
  UI test project exists) `ui-tests`-green.

### Acceptance criteria owned by this slice

- **AC-U4.1:** After editing a source field, the source model MUST update via
  `SourceEditorView.update` and the live Stokes/ellipse readout MUST refresh.
- **AC-U4.2:** After choosing a polarization preset, the ellipse (`AvaPlot`) and
  Poincaré (`WebView2`) views MUST refresh from `liveStokes`/`poincareMarker`.

### Files in scope owned by this slice

- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/SourceView.fs` (new) — sources panel view.

### File:line references owned by this slice

- `SourceEditorView.SourceMsg` (`Sources/SourceEditorView.fs:45`: `SetWaveLength`/`SetIncidenceAngleDegrees`/`SetPolarization`/`SetEllipticity`/`SetIntensity`/`SetDisplayUnit`); `SourceEditorView.update` (`SourceEditorView.fs:59`); `SourceEditorView.defaultSource` (`SourceEditorView.fs:107`).
- `PolarizationPicker.applyPreset` (`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/Sources/PolarizationPicker.fs:46`); `PolarizationPicker.liveStokes` (`PolarizationPicker.fs:82`); `poincareMarker` (`PolarizationPicker.fs:98`); `ellipseParameters` (`PolarizationPicker.fs:109`).
- `PolarizationPlots.renderEllipse` (`Charts/PolarizationPlots.fs:39`, returns `ScottPlot.Plot`); `PolarizationPlots.poincareSphere` (`Charts/PolarizationPlots.fs:57`, returns `Plotly.NET.GenericChart`).

## Scope

The sources panel edits the light source and its polarization, with a live
Stokes / Poincaré / ellipse readout. The editor reducer, presets, and live
projections exist; this slice renders the fields and hosts the ellipse in the
`AvaPlot` adapter and the Poincaré sphere in the WebView2 adapter (both from
slice 002 / U5.1).

## Requirements

### R-1. U4.1 — Source editor fields

The `sources` panel view MUST render fields that dispatch
`SourceEditorView.SourceMsg` (`Sources/SourceEditorView.fs:45`:
`SetWaveLength`/`SetIncidenceAngleDegrees`/`SetPolarization`/`SetEllipticity`/
`SetIntensity`/`SetDisplayUnit`) as `Source …`, routed through
`SourceEditorView.update` (`SourceEditorView.fs:59`), seeded from
`SourceEditorView.defaultSource` (`SourceEditorView.fs:107`) for a new source.

### R-2. U4.2 — Polarization presets and live readout

The view MUST offer the polarization presets via `PolarizationPicker.applyPreset`
(`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/Sources/PolarizationPicker.fs:46`)
and render the live readout from `PolarizationPicker.liveStokes`
(`PolarizationPicker.fs:82`), `poincareMarker` (`PolarizationPicker.fs:98`), and
`ellipseParameters` (`PolarizationPicker.fs:109`). The polarization ellipse
(`PolarizationPlots.renderEllipse`, `Charts/PolarizationPlots.fs:39`, returns
`ScottPlot.Plot`) MUST be hosted in an `AvaPlot`; the Poincaré sphere
(`PolarizationPlots.poincareSphere`, `Charts/PolarizationPlots.fs:57`, returns
`Plotly.NET.GenericChart`) MUST be hosted in the WebView2 adapter.

## Non-requirements

- Does NOT re-implement the source reducer or the polarization projections.
- Does NOT host the ellipse in WebView2 or the Poincaré sphere in `AvaPlot`
  (ellipse → `AvaPlot`; Poincaré → WebView2).
- Does NOT embed its own renderer hosting; it reuses `ChartHosts.fs` (slice 002).
- Does NOT edit any frozen core module (§0.1).

