## Testing plan

Gates that apply to this slice (run in order; first failure short-circuits):
`build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`, `impl-log-structure`,
`state-of-world-structure`, `ui-smoke`, `ui-tests`.

- `ui-tests`: a sources-panel headless view test asserts a field edit dispatches
  `Source …` and the live Stokes/ellipse readout refreshes (AC-U4.1), and a preset
  choice refreshes the ellipse (`AvaPlot`) and Poincaré (`WebView2`) from
  `liveStokes`/`poincareMarker` (AC-U4.2).
- `ui-smoke`: the `sources` panel renders one frame headlessly; the AvaPlot /
  WebView2 hosts degrade to "unavailable" placeholders when absent (§U1.8).
- `build`, `constructor-unit-tests`, `unit-tests`: green; no frozen edits.

## Risks

- **Low–medium.** Reducer, presets, and projections all exist; the worry is
  hosting two different renderer kinds (ScottPlot ellipse vs Plotly Poincaré)
  correctly through the two `ChartHosts.fs` adapters and degrading both gracefully
  under headless (§U1.8).

## Hand-off

- The `sources` panel and the `Source` `RootMsg` case are wired.
- Emit the state-of-the-world `gates:` YAML block with this round's baseline
  counts so the next slice's `count_at_least` gates have a baseline.
